<statement>
<p>
Indicate whether the following are true or false.
<ol marker="(a)">
<li>
<p>
 <m>3</m> is prime and <m>3</m> is even.
    </p></li>
<li>
<p>
 <m>3</m> is prime or <m>3</m> is even.
    </p></li>
<li>
<p>
 For <m>x\in \mathbb{R}</m>, <m>x^2 > x</m> when <m>x>1</m>, and <m>18</m> is composite.
    </p></li>
<li>
<p>
 For <m>x\in \mathbb{R}</m>, <m>x^2 > x</m> when <m>x>1</m>, or <m>18</m> is composite.
</p>

</li>
</ol>
</p>
</statement>
<solution>
<p>
<ol marker="(a)">
<li>
<p>
 False. The statement <q><m>3</m> is even</q> is false, so the conjunction is false.
    </p></li>
<li>
<p>
 True. The statement <q><m>3</m> is prime</q> is true, so the disjunction is true.
    </p></li>
<li>
<p>
 True. Both of the statements <q><m>x^2 > x</m> when <m>x>1</m></q> and <q><m>18</m> is composite</q> are true, so the conjunction is true.
    </p></li>
<li>
<p>
 True. Both of the statements <q><m>x^2 > x</m> when <m>x>1</m></q> and <q><m>18</m> is composite</q> are true, so the disjunction is also true.
</p>
</li>
</ol>
</p>
</solution>
</exercise>
